# Zeno Classic Launcher — Cline AI Rules

## MANDATORY RULES — Follow for every code change

### No Worktrees
Never use git worktrees. Always work directly in the main repo directory.

### Full Workflow After Every Code Change

1. Full release build (ALWAYS assembleRelease, never partial):
   export JAVA_HOME="/Applications/Android Studio.app/Contents/jbr/Contents/Home"
   ./gradlew assembleRelease --no-daemon

2. Install on device:
   adb install -r "app/build/outputs/apk/release/Zeno Classic.apk"
   (shortcut: ./scripts/build-install.sh does both)

3. Ask user to test — wait for confirmation before committing.

4. Commit ONLY after user confirms:
   git add <specific files>
   git commit -m "description"

5. After commit: git rev-list --count @{u}..HEAD
   - <5 ahead: stay local
   - ≥5 ahead: remind user to push to remote

### Never
- Use git worktrees
- Run partial builds for device testing
- Commit before user confirms device test
- Use git add . or git add -A
- Force-push main
